  "text": "PKCδ is ubiquitously expressed and activated in response to a broad variety of stimuli. In response to specific stimuli, several tyrosine residues in PKCδ can be phosphorylated by different tyrosine kinases ( Fig. 1 ), leading to individual phosphorylation patterns and possibly differential activation of downstream targets. Among its main roles, PKCδ is responsible for the regulation of survival, proliferation, and apoptosis in a variety of cells including lymphocytes (reviewed in [CITATION_1] ) (Fig. 2) .",
